  "text": "To explain why marsh harriers are more flexible in space than in time, we may have to consider the predictability of the relevant environmental cues. Efficient long-distance navigation between the fixed breeding and wintering locations may permit a high degree of adaptive route flexibility in relation to unpredictable conditions en route. By contrast, photoperiod, an entirely predictable 'Zeitgeber' for migration (cf. [CITATION_1] ), as well as favourable, area-specific 'climatic windows' may contribute to highly repeatable individual schedules. Focusing on the spatial and temporal variability and the ways in which it can be correlated with environmental conditions can further our understanding about the scope of flexibility in migratory behaviour.",
